  "response_text": "# Quick & Healthy Weekly Meal Plan (20 min/day)\n\n## Strategy\n- **Sunday prep**: 30 min of chopping/cooking base ingredients\n- **Weekday cooking**: Simple assembly and quick cooking\n- **Freezer-friendly**: Most meals reheat well\n\n---\n\n## Sunday Prep (30 minutes)\n- Cook 2 cups brown rice\n- Grill/bake 2 lbs chicken breast\n- Roast sheet pan: broccoli, bell peppers, sweet potato\n- Cook 1 pot lentil soup\n\n---\n\n## Daily Meal Ideas\n\n### **Monday**\n- **Breakfast**: Overnight oats (prep night before)\n- **Lunch**: Chicken + rice + roasted veggies\n- **Dinner**: Pasta with jarred marinara, frozen spinach (15 min)\n\n### **Tuesday**\n- **Breakfast**: Yogurt + granola + berries\n- **Lunch**: Lentil soup + whole grain bread\n- **Dinner**: Stir-fry (prep veggies, cook noodles, add protein) (18 min)\n\n### **Wednesday**\n- **Breakfast**: Scrambled eggs + toast\n- **Lunch**: Chicken grain bowl with roasted veggies\n- **Dinner**: Quesadillas with canned beans + cheese (12 min)\n\n### **Thursday**\n- **Breakfast**: Smoothie (frozen fruit, yogurt, spinach)\n- **Lunch**: Lentil soup + salad\n- **Dinner**: Canned tuna + whole wheat pasta + frozen peas (15 min)\n\n### **Friday**\n- **Breakfast**: Cereal + milk + fruit\n- **Lunch**: Leftover stir-fry\n- **Dinner**: **Treat yourself**: Order out or simple frozen pizza\n\n### **Saturday**\n- **Breakfast**: Pancakes (frozen, reheat)\n- **Lunch**: Chickpea salad (canned chickpeas, cucumber, tomato, dressing)\n- **Dinner**: Egg fried rice with frozen veggies (16 min)\n\n### **Sunday**\n- **Breakfast**: Avocado toast\n- **Lunch**: Meal prep for next week\n- **Dinner**: Sheet pan salmon + roasted vegetables (20 min)\n\n---\n\n## Time-Saving Staples\n✓ Canned beans, lentils, tuna  \n✓ Frozen vegetables & fruit  \n✓ Rotisserie chicken (when short on time)  \n✓ Jarred sauces, peanut butter  \n✓ Eggs, Greek yogurt, cheese  \n✓ Quick-cook grains (rice, pasta, instant oats)  \n✓ Pre-cut veggies (when budget allows)\n\n---\n\n## Budget Tips\n- Buy rice/pasta in bulk\n- Choose eggs as affordable protein\n- Use seasonal produce\n- Buy store brands\n\nThis plan balances nutrition, convenience, and realistic college life!",
